      "writtenOn": "2026-06-10T13:19:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Can we factor the L34/flow-hash tuple extraction instead of duplicating the outer hash paths?\nhash_eth_l34_inner_inline() copies most of hash_eth_l34_inline() just to add the inner-peek case. It would be cleaner to split this into an Ethernet wrapper plus IP-only L34 helpers, so the inner-aware path can call the IP helper for IPinIP/IPv6-in-IP and the Ethernet/IP helper for GRE TEB/NVGRE as appropriate.\nSame idea applies to ip4_compute_flow_hash() / ip6_compute_flow_hash(): normalize “outer or resolved inner header” into a small descriptor, then feed that into the existing v4/v6 hash mixing logic. That should reduce drift risk and make fixes like IPv4 IHL/total-length validation live in one place.",
      "revId": "5e18b8ad42220079b497320ac09df74dc425c82b",
      "serverId": "6d2eb258-4fe2-443e-8a38-ca81da23d4c2"
    },
